olive oil
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 Brown Onion
1 packet chicken breast
1 tsp honey
2 flatbreads
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
2 clove garlic
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and parsnip into bite-sized chunks.
Slice onion into wedges.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray, sprinkle over
mild North Indian spice blend, drizzle with
olive oil and toss to coat. Spread out evenly and
roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

Little cooks: Help toss the veggies.

• Finely chop garlic. In a large frying pan, heat
a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl, then add
Greek-style yoghurt and stir to combine.
Season to taste.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the
ingredients!

• In a medium bowl, combine Mumbai spice
blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken
breast and turn to coat. Season with salt
and pepper.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until browned,
2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray,
drizzle over the honey, then bake until cooked
through, 8-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink in the middle.

• Cut flatbreads into bite-sized pieces.
• When veggies have 10 minutes remaining,
scatter flatbread on the tray with the veggies.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and
pepper and roast until golden.

• When the veggies are done, add baby
spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine
vinegar to the tray.
• Gently toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice honey-glazed Indian chicken.
• Divide roast veggie and flatbread salad between
bowls. Top with chicken.
• Serve with garlic yoghurt. Enjoy!